{"title_page": "Hwasa", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{short description|South Korean singer}}\n{{Korean name|Ahn}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Hwasa\n| image              = 170923 \ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 29.jpg\n| image_size         = \n| caption            = Hwasa in September 2017\n| native_name        = \ud654\uc0ac\n| birth_name         = Ahn Hye-jin\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1995|07|23}}\n| birth_place        = [[Jeonju]], [[North Jeolla Province|Jeollabuk-do]], South Korea\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Singer|rapper|songwriter}}\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist\n| embed           = yes\n| background      = solo_singer\n| genre           = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[jazz]]|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]}}\n| instrument      = Vocals\n| years_active    = 2014\u2013present\n| label           = [[RBW (company)|RBW]]\n| associated_acts = [[Mamamoo]]\n| module          = {{Infobox Korean name\n|title       = [[Korean name]]\n|hangul      = {{linktext|\uc548|\ud61c|\uc9c4}}\n|hanja       = {{linktext|\u5b89|\u60e0|\u771e}}\n|rr          = An Hye-jin\n|mr          = Ahn Hyechin\n|hangulstage = {{linktext|\ud654|\uc0ac}}\n|hanjastage  = \n|rrstage     = Hwasa\n|mrstage     = Hwasa\n|child       = yes}}}}\n}}\n\n'''Ahn Hye-jin''' (born July 23, 1995),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/283703|title=My Name, \ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 (1)|publisher=Ten Asia|language=ko|date=July 15, 2014}}</ref> better known by her stage name '''Hwasa''', is a South Korean singer, songwriter, rapper and television personality signed under [[RBW (company)|RBW]]. She debuted as a member of the girl group [[Mamamoo]] in June 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wowtv.co.kr/newscenter/news/view.asp?bcode=T30001000&artid=A201406270517|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \uadf8\ub8f9\uba85 \ubb34\uc2a8\ub73b? \uc544\uc774\uc720 \uc874\uacbd\ud558\ub294 '4\uc778\uc870 \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9'|publisher=Wow TV|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nAhn Hye-jin was born on July 23, 1995 in [[Jeonju]], [[North Jeolla Province|Jeollabuk-do]], South Korea,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?where=nexearch&query=%ED%99%94%EC%82%AC&sm=ppl_cts&ie=utf8&key=PeopleService&os=1727126|title=\ud654\uc0ac \ud504\ub85c\ud544|publisher=Naver|language=ko}}</ref> where she lived with her parents and two elder sisters. She graduated from Wonkwang Information Arts High School.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://khmusic.co.kr/about/notice.php?page=1&mode=view&PGn=16&iKeyNum=1&strSkin=notice&pgCode=&SVALUE=YToyOntzOjg6ImtleWZpZWxkIjtzOjc6InN1YmplY3QiO3M6Mzoia2V5IjtzOjA6IiI7fQ==|title=\uacbd\ud76c\uc2e4\uc6a9\uc74c\uc545\ud559\uc6d0 \ud569\uaca9\uc0dd \uba85\ub2e8\uc740 \uc2e0\ub8b0\ud560 \uc218 \uc788\uc2b5\ub2c8\ub2e4.|publisher=KH Music|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nEven before her K-pop debut, a number of South Korean artists \u2013 including [[Solbi]] and the band [[Standing Egg]] \u2013 recognised her talent and featured her on their tracks when she was 16.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zlEdKi8MYBs|title=Standing egg - \ub10c \uc774\ubcc4 \ub09c \uc544\uc9c1|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\nHwasa debuted as a member of the girl group [[Mamamoo]] on June 19, 2014, being one of the leading voices with the release of the lead single \"Mr. Ambiguous\" from their first extended play (EP) ''Hello''. She wrote and composed \"My Heart/I Do Me\" from ''Hello''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vibe.naver.com/track/4284580|title=NAVER VIBE(\ubc14\uc774\ube0c)|last=|first=|date=|website=vibe.naver.com|language=ko|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2018 she joined the cast of [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]] reality television show ''[[Hyena on the Keyboard]]''; the appearance spawned a collaboration with rapper [[Loco (rapper)|Loco]] titled \"Don't\". Hwasa took part in writing and composing the song and it successfully topped the South Korean's [[Gaon Digital Chart]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.melon.com/song/detail.htm?songId=31035061&ref=etc&snsGate=Y|title=\uc8fc\uc9c0\ub9c8|website=www.melon.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> The song was later certified Platinum.<ref name=\"Don't&quot;download&quot;\" />\n\nIn February 2019, Hwasa made her debut as a solo artist with the digital single, \"Twit\" which she participated in writing and composing it.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.melon.com/song/detail.htm?songId=31608765|title=\uba4d\uccad\uc774(twit)|website=www.melon.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> The song successfully topped the Gaon Digital Chart and scored a \"Triple Crown\", topping the Gaon Digital, Gaon Download and Gaon Streaming charts in Korea.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mosen.mt.co.kr/article/G1111090329|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \ud654\uc0ac, \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4\uace1 '\uba4d\uccad\uc774'\ub85c \uac00\uc628\ucc28\ud2b8 3\uad00\uc655|last=OSEN|date=2019-02-28|website=mosen.mt.co.kr|language=ko|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> Hwasa also composed and wrote the song \"In The Fall\" and was released in October 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m2.melon.com/song/detail.htm?songId=32090955|title=\uac00\uc744\uc18d\uc5d0\uc11c|website=m2.melon.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> In March 2020, Hwasa teamed up with an English singer [[Dua Lipa]] for a new remix version of \"Physical\" which includes Korean lyrics.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/international/9335384/dua-lipa-mamamoo-hwa-sa-physical-kpop-remix?utm_medium=social&utm_source=twitter|title=Dua Lipa & Mamamoo&#39;s Hwasa&#39;s &#39;Physical&#39; Remix: Listen|date=2020-03-18|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jeffbenjamin/2020/03/18/dua-lipa-physical-remix-hwasa-mamamoo-kpop/|title=Dua Lipa Taps Into The K-Pop World Again With \u2018Physical\u2019 Remix Featuring Hwa Sa Of MAMAMOO|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\n== Other ventures ==\n=== Endorsements ===\n\nDuring her first appearance on ''I Live Alone'' in June 2018, Hwasa started a national \"Gopchang craze\", causing the delicacy to sell out across the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20180621000814|title=[Trending] K-pop star sparks 'cow intestines' craze in Korea|last=Herald|first=The Korea|date=June 21, 2018|website=www.koreaherald.com|language=en|access-date=February 25, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/magazines/style/people-events/article/2157952/how-k-pop-star-hwasa-turned-goddess-after-eating-beef|title=K-pop star Hwasa turns into a 'goddess' \u2013 after eating beef intestines|date=August 2, 2018|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=February 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2018, Hwasa became the ambassador for outdoor brand [[The North Face]] for the 2018 fashion week season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/018/0004210454|title='\uc644\ud310 \uc694\uc815' \ud654\uc0ac, \ub178\uc2a4\ud398\uc774\uc2a4 \ud64d\ubcf4\ub300\uc0ac \ubc1c\ud0c1|website=n.news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> In October 2018, she became the first female model for [[Lotte Corporation|Lotte]] Crunky Gold since its release in 1984.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&oid=029&aid=0002489311&sid1=001|title=\ub86f\ub370\uc81c\uacfc, \ud06c\ub7f0\ud0a4 \uc0c8 \ubaa8\ub378\ub85c \u2018\uba39\ubc29\uc694\uc815\u2019 \ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \ud654\uc0ac \uc120\uc815|website=news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> \n\nIn March 2019, [[Coca-Cola]]'s ice tea brand Gold Peak Tea selected Hwasa as their new model.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&oid=076&aid=0003397375&sid1=001|title=\ucf54\uce74-\ucf5c\ub77c\uc0ac \uace8\ub4dc\ud53c\ud06c \ud2f0(TEA), \ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \u2018\ud654\uc0ac\u2019 \ubaa8\ub378 \ubc1c\ud0c1|website=news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> She then became the newest muse for make up brand Rarekind in April 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&oid=014&aid=0004201900&sid1=001|title=\ub808\uc5b4\uce74\uc778\ub4dc, \ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc \ubba4\uc988\uc5d0 \ub300\uc138 \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 \ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \u2018\ud654\uc0ac\u2019 \ubc1c\ud0c1|website=news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> In June 2019, Hwasa became the new model for [[Everland]] Caribbean Bay.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/408/0000074466|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \ud654\uc0ac, \uc6cc\ud130\ud30c\ud06c \uad11\uace0\uae4c\uc9c0 \uc811\uc218... 2019 \uc5ec\ub984 \ucc45\uc784\uc9c4\ub2e4!|website=n.news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> Hwasa was featured on the cover of [[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|''Cosmopolitan'']] Korea's August 2019 issue.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/photo/read?cid=846241&oid=009&aid=0004394198|title=\ud654\uc0ac, \uac74\uac15\u7f8e \ub118\uce58\ub294 \u2018\ud0c4\ud0c4 \ubcf5\uadfc\u2019(\ud654\ubcf4)|website=entertain.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> She later teamed up with [[Vogue (magazine)|''Vogue'']] magazine in November and [[Urban Decay (cosmetics)|Urban Decay]] cosmetics for their \"Pretty Different\" and \"Queen\" inspired concepts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/photo/read?cid=846241&oid=112&aid=0003225933|title=\ud654\uc0ac, \uac15\ub82c\ud558\uace0 \ub300\ub2f4\ud55c \ubd84\uc704\uae30..'\ud654\uc5fc\ubcf4\ub2e4 \ub728\uac70\uc6b4 \ud654\uc0ac\u2019 [\ud654\ubcf4]|website=entertain.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vogue.co.kr/2019/10/28/diversity-of-beauty-2/|title=\uc544\ub984\ub2e4\uc6c0\uc758 \ub2e4\uc591\uc131 \u2013 \ud654\uc0ac {{!}} \ubcf4\uadf8 \ucf54\ub9ac\uc544 (Vogue Korea)|last=voguedigital|date=2019-10-28|website=Vogue Korea|language=ko-KR|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> [[Ottogi]] revealed in November 2019 that their newest model for their [[Jjamppong]] instant noodles was Hwasa.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lawissue.co.kr/view.php?ud=201911220926207426204ead0791_12|title=\uc9ec\ubf55\ub77c\uba74 \ub3cc\ud48d\uc758 \uc8fc\uc778\uacf5 \uc624\ub69c\uae30 \u2018\uc9c4\uc9ec\ubf55\u2019 \ub9ac\ub274\uc5bc \ucd9c\uc2dc|date=2019-11-22|website=\ub85c\uc774\uc288|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\nIn 2020, Hwasa collaborated with [[The Sims 4]] for their advertising campaign.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamemeca.com/view.php?gid=1613561|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 '\ud654\uc0ac'\uac00 \uc2ec\uc988 4\ub97c \ud558\ub294 \uc774\uc720, CF \uc601\uc0c1 \uacf5\uac1c|website=www.gamemeca.com|language=ko-KR|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> She then teamed up with [[MCM Worldwide|MCM]] for the February issue of [[Elle (magazine)|''Elle'']] Korea's<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/109/0004151658|title=\ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34 \ud654\uc0ac\uac00 \uc815\uc758\ud55c 'HIP', \uc790\uc720\ubd84\ubc29\ud55c \ud3ec\uc2a4\ud038[\ud654\ubcf4]|website=n.news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> Hwasa is also an ambassador for sports brand [[Adidas]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/144/0000658571|title=\uc190\ud765\ubbfcX\ud654\uc0acX\uc774\uc815\ud6c4, \uc544\ub514\ub2e4\uc2a4 \ub7ec\ub2dd \ucea0\ud398\uc778 \ubaa8\ub378 \uc120\uc815 [\uacf5\uc2dd]|website=n.news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/112/0003272421|title=\ud654\uc0ac, \uac74\uac15\ud55c \uc139\uc2dc\u7f8e\u2192\ub3c5\ubcf4\uc801\uc778 \uc6b0\uc544\ud568..\ud56b\ud55c \uc2a4\ud0c0\uc77c \uc544\uc774\ucf58 \ub4f1\uadf9[\ud654\ubcf4]|website=n.news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\n=== Public Image ===\n\nHwasa's first appearance on ''I Live Alone'' has earned her the titles \"Gopchang Goddess\" and \"Hwasa Effect\". <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20180621000814|title=[Trending] K-pop star sparks \u2018cow intestines\u2019 craze in Korea|last=Herald|first=The Korea|date=2018-06-21|website=www.koreaherald.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/magazines/style/people-events/article/2157952/how-k-pop-star-hwasa-turned-goddess-after-eating-beef|title=K-pop star Hwasa turns into a \u2018goddess\u2019 \u2013 after eating beef intestines|date=2018-08-02|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> Since then, Hwasa has managed to sell out every item she uses in her screen time, including recorder music sheets, Gopchang, even her fried tofu rice ball for dieting.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.insight.co.kr/news/272641|title=\u2018\ub098\ud63c\uc0b0\u2019\uc11c \ub9ac\ucf54\ub354 \ubd80\ub294 \ubaa8\uc2b5\uc73c\ub85c \uc545\ubcf4\uae4c\uc9c0 \u2018\uc8fc\ubb38 \ud3ed\uc8fc\u2019 \uc2dc\ucf1c\ubc84\ub9b0 \ud654\uc0ac|date=2020-03-09|website=\uc778\uc0ac\uc774\ud2b8|language=ko|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{See also|Mamamoo discography}}\n\n===Singles===\n====As lead artist====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of singles, with selected chart positions, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:1em;\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"4\" style=\"width:5em;\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\" | Sales\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:15em;\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"|[[Gaon Music Chart|KOR]]</small><br><ref name=\"gaon_digital_chart\">{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/o